Where even to begin!!! 1, hard to understand his accent. 2, not clear at all on learning objectives. 3, boring voice. 4, lecture notes were useless - it doesnt cover the exam questions, 5, easily distracted - always go off the topic.  DONT TAKE HIS CLASS!!! THE END.
No need to go to the class, textbook is very clear. Assignments and tests are easy. Professor is boring and doesnt get along with technology :)
Decent professor. Assignments and tests are fairly easy. Very easy to get a good mark as long are you're not lazy or an idiot.

He teaches absolutely nothing more than what you need to know that was already said in the textbook. His lectures are boring, his use of examples are below mediocrity, and he does nothing to elaborate or clarify anything in the textbook. Tests are your usual UofT material.
Best Prof I ever had. Very clear in contexts, provide great help!! His classes are amazing!

Terrible, terrible professor. Barely speaks proper english. No need to go to class, read the book and you're guranteed a good mark. He just shows up for an hour lecture, has powerpoints outlining the textbook and then leaves.

gpa booster!!!

Took stats with this guy. Could not understand a damned thing sometimes because of his accent. My suggestion- take this class just to get through it for the course requirement. Do your readings, pay attention to the lectures somewhat and get extra help from your t.a.'s (and you will) when needed. Tests are fair.Complex mathematics kept to a minimum
Ugh, so boring to listen to. Lecture was pretty much pointless. Read the textbook and got a good mark though.

Overall a good Professor. Very clear about whats on the tests. Straightforward questions. Do the readings and take notes in lecture and its not hard to get an A without tons of studying. If you make a good argument, he'll change your mark (changed mine from 80 to 85 on one test). Topics range from fairly interesting to painfully boring. Worth it.

Decent Prof, Decent course. I get how people who took stats w/ him don't like him, who likes their stats prof? Excellent course for boosting your GPA while not consuming all your time.Nice guy too

Prof Fong is one of the most approachable profs you will ever find at U of T. His tests are fair and his lecture topics are quite interesting.
